FBIS4-16782 "drsov076_b_94030" FBIS-SOV-94-076 Daily Report 19 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Duty To Be Imposed on Petroleum Production Duty To Be Imposed on Petroleum Production PM2004115594 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 19 Apr 94 p 1 PM2004115594 Moscow IZVESTIYA Russian BFN [ITAR-TASS report: "New Excise Rate Per Tonne of Oil Sold"] [Text] As of 1 May this year the Russian Government is establishing an excise rate for extracting enterprises of, on average, 14,750 rubles per tonne of oil, including gas condensate. This amount will change monthly, depending on the change in the rate of the ruble against the U.S. dollar. There will be different rates for individual oil and gas extracting enterprises.
